result.execSummary:
The defendant Laurel J Holbach was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Laurel J Holbach in court with attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Court ordered SENTENCE WITHHELD and placed the defendant on probation for  12 months, concurrent to current probation, with the following conditions:
*Perform 100 hours of community service with a non-profit organization. 
*Defendant to pay $200.00 DNA surcharge by 02-22-2016 or civil judgment.  Court WAIVES all other costs, fees and surcharges due to indegency.  
Court grants transfer or probation to Sheboygan County.  
Appeal rights given.

Attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer in court.  Elizabeth Longo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Matter before court for plea/sentencing hearing.  Statements by defense counsel that defendant is unable to appear due to medical issues.  Defense requests an adjourned plea/sentencing date with a stayed bench warrant.  Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until the next court date.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for May 21, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Laurel J Holbach in court with attorney Jamie Francis Cimpl-Wiemer.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case held off the record.   Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea and sentencing in Branch 46. jks
  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for 04-15-2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant advised if released from custody it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping, a warrant issued or high cash bail.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with ANY WAL-MART.
  Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Laurel J Holbach in court with attorney Joel H. Rosenthal.  Defendant Laurel J Holbach in custody.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk:  hgj.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Branch 46.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for February 26, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
